1
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:34,900
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:37,830
[Episode 2]

3
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:44,450
You still have the nerve to smile.

4
00:01:46,150 --> 00:01:48,039
You heartless thing.

5
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:51,400
When you can't make it out there anymore

6
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:54,150
and come crawling back
with your tail between your legs,

7
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:54,840
I will

8
00:01:56,229 --> 00:01:57,710
give you a good scolding.

9
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:09,169
Zhang Jiaming,

10
00:02:09,710 --> 00:02:10,509
you lied to me.

11
00:02:11,150 --> 00:02:13,010
I thought you had really changed.

12
00:02:19,870 --> 00:02:26,170
♪ Walk on the same road a thousand times ♪

13
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:33,640
♪ Run together and venture
to the distant mountains ♪

14
00:02:34,210 --> 00:02:40,720
♪ We yearn for tomorrow
yet cling to yesterday ♪

15
00:02:41,910 --> 00:02:47,060
♪ Leaves blown away by the wind ♪

16
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:52,200
♪ If seas turn to mulberry fields ♪

17
00:02:52,220 --> 00:02:55,550
♪ Whether flat or winding ♪

18
00:02:55,570 --> 00:02:59,300
♪ If rain wets your face ♪

19
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:05,200
♪ Chat at the old spot
after all storms have passed ♪

20
00:03:03,030 --> 00:03:03,750
Wait, wait.

21
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,360
I feel like I'm about to fly.

22
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:10,400
♪ Time train goes round and round ♪

23
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,840
If I could fly,

24
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:10,430
I would fly to Zhang Jiaming
and that witch.

25
00:03:10,420 --> 00:03:13,440
♪ Day by day, year by year ♪

26
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:12,800
Because I can't understand it,

27
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,870
no matter how hard I try.

28
00:03:13,770 --> 00:03:17,600
♪ Wave your hands and stride ahead ♪

29
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:15,630
I want to find my dad

30
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:17,110
and ask for the reason

31
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:18,360
in person.

32
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:21,320
♪ There'll be sunshine through the years ♪

33
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:21,030
Yes, we'll go with you.

34
00:03:21,350 --> 00:03:24,560
♪ Migratory birds fly over
the mountain top ♪

35
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:28,510
♪ Survive the coldest day ♪

36
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:33,770
♪ Wait till the kapok blooms ♪

37
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,870
Zhang Xiaoman is clueless!

38
00:03:33,030 --> 00:03:34,590
Yan Xiaodan, you stay right there!

39
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:37,570
♪ When you come rushing back still ♪

40
00:03:37,950 --> 00:03:40,320
♪ The young you ♪

41
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,930
Let me tell you guys.

42
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,570
I love bridges the most.

43
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,630
Why's that?

44
00:03:44,910 --> 00:03:47,750
I think bridges are magical things.

45
00:03:48,190 --> 00:03:50,190
They connect two different places.

46
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:52,520
Shouldn't you prefer railways then?

47
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,920
Railways are different.

48
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,560
Railways need tracks.

49
00:03:56,430 --> 00:03:58,090
No matter how far we want to go,

50
00:03:58,210 --> 00:04:00,360
we can only
move forward along that track.

51
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,560
You can't deviate even a bit.

52
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:04,150
But bridges feel mysterious!

53
00:04:05,710 --> 00:04:07,840
Even if the two sides aren't far apart,

54
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:10,710
I'm always curious
about what's on the other side.

55
00:04:11,530 --> 00:04:12,340
But...

56
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,800
don't both sides look the same?

57
00:04:15,150 --> 00:04:16,810
I grew up near the old factory.

58
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:20,920
I came from the old factory
to the East Chemical Plant.

59
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:23,530
I actually know where I want to go

60
00:04:23,890 --> 00:04:25,020
and what I want to do.

61
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,080
Nothing to be curious about.

62
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:29,790
But I've never known
what Tiecheng looks like.

63
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:32,150
I can't help but imagine

64
00:04:32,170 --> 00:04:33,270
what beautiful things,

65
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:35,480
fun things, and delicious food are there.

66
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,750
Our factory has everything we need.

67
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:38,150
What's so good out there?

68
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,330
Xiaodan, what do you think?

69
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:42,510
I like the Mahavira Hall

70
00:04:42,909 --> 00:04:45,240
because it's the highest place
in our factory.

71
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:47,950
Standing there, you can see
not only our factory

72
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:50,040
but also the distant mountains.

73
00:04:50,310 --> 00:04:51,430
If it were higher,

74
00:04:51,510 --> 00:04:53,950
we could see
what's in those far-away places.

75
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:55,070
Anyway, whatever,

76
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:57,240
no other place is as good as our factory.

77
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,000
I'm not talking to you anymore.

78
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,400
You don't know anything.

79
00:04:59,470 --> 00:05:00,220
Traitor!

80
00:05:01,270 --> 00:05:01,950
Xiaoman!

81
00:05:02,990 --> 00:05:03,720
Xiaoman!

82
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:04,870
Zhang Xiaoman!

83
00:05:05,070 --> 00:05:05,930
Zhang Xiaoman!

84
00:05:06,270 --> 00:05:07,330
Just like my dad!

85
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:08,560
Why are you running so fast?

86
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,240
I'm not talking to you guys anymore!

87
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,510
This is so worrying.

88
00:05:11,510 --> 00:05:13,160
Where could they have gone?

89
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:14,800
You're lucky.

90
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,950
Yours are boys.

91
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:18,670
Mine's a girl. I'm even more worried.

92
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:21,430
Yan, what did the school say?

93
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:23,490
Alright, I've found out everything.

94
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,830
The kid named...

95
00:05:24,830 --> 00:05:26,090
Wang Dongdong told me.

96
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,560
Jiaming left, didn't he?

97
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:31,800
Xiaoman insisted on finding his father.

98
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:35,450
Xia Lei and Xiaodan went with him.

99
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:38,040
The three of them
must be together right now.

100
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,920
What if the kids have gotten lost
in the mountains?

101
00:05:42,390 --> 00:05:44,000
What if they have nothing to eat or drink

102
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,159
in the mountains late at night?

103
00:05:45,159 --> 00:05:46,630
Then we'll just have to go look for them.

104
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,830
Don't panic, everyone.

105
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:48,430
Stay calm.

106
00:05:48,430 --> 00:05:49,840
Let me think. Let me think.

107
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:50,950
Here's what we'll do.

108
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:51,680
We'll split up.

109
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,310
You drive to Tiecheng.

110
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:53,950
Okay.

111
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:54,390
Alright?

112
00:05:54,390 --> 00:05:56,190
Between Tiecheng and the bus station,

113
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:57,310
search several times,

114
00:05:57,310 --> 00:05:57,750
okay?

115
00:05:57,750 --> 00:05:58,950
I'll get some people

116
00:05:58,950 --> 00:06:00,510
to search for them
in the mountains, alright?

117
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:01,710
Then I'll go with you.

118
00:06:01,830 --> 00:06:03,000
Don't make things more difficult.

119
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,120
Just stay home.

120
00:06:04,190 --> 00:06:05,270
Someone needs to be at the house.

121
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:06,190
What if they come back?

122
00:06:06,190 --> 00:06:06,610
Right.

123
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,110
You two as well. Go home.

124
00:06:08,110 --> 00:06:08,390
Right.

125
00:06:08,390 --> 00:06:08,920
Okay?

126
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:09,680
Wait for my news.

127
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:10,390
Alright. Let's go.

128
00:06:10,390 --> 00:06:11,000
I...

129
00:06:11,310 --> 00:06:12,560
What if they come back?

130
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,680
We'll keep in touch

131
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:14,940
and update each other.

132
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:16,310
Move! Everyone move!

133
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,190
Kids, hide!

134
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:18,310
Mr. Ding is back!

135
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,680
Quick! Quick!

136
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,000
Kids, quick!

137
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,630
Good luck, Mr. Ding!

138
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:23,800
Go home for your meals!

139
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,630
Good luck, Mr. Ding!

140
00:06:24,630 --> 00:06:25,960
No problem! No problem!

141
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:28,360
Alright! Alright!

142
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:33,620
Hurry up, come on.

143
00:06:33,620 --> 00:06:34,510
I-I know.

144
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,560
Right away. Right away.

145
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,310
What do you mean by "right away"?

146
00:06:36,310 --> 00:06:37,270
I just got an injection at the hospital.

147
00:06:37,270 --> 00:06:37,830
Hurry up, come on.

148
00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:38,430
What are you doing?

149
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:39,680
Come on. What is it?

150
00:06:40,310 --> 00:06:40,750
Don't.

151
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,730
Close the curtains!

152
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:45,360
Curtains! Curtains!

153
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:46,780
Let me take it off. Let me.

154
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,020
This neck warmer is too tight.

155
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:50,159
Is it too tight?

156
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:53,530
Well, I made it tight
so the wind won't get in.

157
00:06:53,530 --> 00:06:54,860
It's not the right time.

158
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,510
Nose, your nose.

159
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:00,800
Attention, comrades! Attention!

160
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:02,480
Children from our factory

161
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,310
have gone missing!

162
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:05,950
Probably in the mountains.

163
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:07,880
We need volunteers to help search!

164
00:07:10,310 --> 00:07:11,310
You go make a meal.

165
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:14,310
I'll go with you.

166
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:17,790
What for? Stay home.

167
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:19,650
You came as well.

168
00:07:20,310 --> 00:07:21,750
-Yan, don't worry.
-Thank you. Really.

169
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:22,630
-Don't worry.
-Thank you. Really.

170
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:24,120
We'll definitely find the children.

171
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,190
Don't worry. Don't worry.

172
00:07:25,190 --> 00:07:25,830
Don't worry.

173
00:07:25,830 --> 00:07:26,360
Thank you.

174
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,760
We'll search right away.

175
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,930
You just got an injection.
Why did you come?

176
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:31,750
Children are missing.
How could I not come?

177
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:32,270
Come on, give me one.

178
00:07:32,270 --> 00:07:32,930
Here, here.

179
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,240
Take 2 batteries,

180
00:07:34,570 --> 00:07:35,710
in case it runs out of power.

181
00:07:35,710 --> 00:07:36,440
Don't worry.

182
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:38,270
Take it slow.

183
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:43,390
Slow down. Slow down.

184
00:07:44,180 --> 00:07:45,500
Can we rest here?

185
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,070
I can't go on.

186
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:48,270
Let's sit for a while.

187
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:51,280
Stop walking.

188
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,159
Let's find a place to hide.

189
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:54,920
Where can we hide?

190
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:58,800
Are we going to spend the night outside?

191
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,560
I'm scared.

192
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:01,110
It's okay, Xiaodan.

193
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:02,450
Xia Lei and I are here.

194
00:08:04,470 --> 00:08:05,070
Xia Lei.

195
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,000
Look, is that a cave?

196
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,290
It seems like it.

197
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:09,040
Let's go in and see.

198
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:09,570
Let's go.

199
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,330
Take it slow.

200
00:08:19,060 --> 00:08:19,660
Ma'am.

201
00:08:20,830 --> 00:08:22,750
How's it going? Have they found them?

202
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:24,080
There are men searching

203
00:08:24,230 --> 00:08:25,630
all over the mountains,

204
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:26,430
looking everywhere.

205
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:27,240
Don't worry.

206
00:08:27,410 --> 00:08:29,150
We were just afraid you'd be worried,

207
00:08:29,150 --> 00:08:30,750
so I came back to check on you.

208
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:33,549
But what about the children tonight?

209
00:08:33,549 --> 00:08:35,360
It's alright, Ma'am.

210
00:08:35,850 --> 00:08:37,210
Haven't you eaten yet?

211
00:08:38,870 --> 00:08:39,510
It's fine.

212
00:08:39,659 --> 00:08:41,460
Let me make you something to eat.

213
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,600
No need. No need.

214
00:08:42,630 --> 00:08:44,120
Don't worry. They'll find them.

215
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,320
Tell them to search faster.

216
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,200
They are. Everyone's searching.

217
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,240
Don't worry. I'll prepare

218
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,840
some food for you right away.

219
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:55,080
This cave is too deep.

220
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:56,430
Maybe we should go back.

221
00:08:56,580 --> 00:08:57,880
Victory is just ahead.

222
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,910
It's all your fault for running around
and getting us into the mountains.

223
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:01,790
Great. Now we're completely lost.

224
00:09:01,790 --> 00:09:04,390
Xiaoman, are we really
sleeping here tonight?

225
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:06,870
We can't go back anyway.

226
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:08,200
Even though we're lost.

227
00:09:08,770 --> 00:09:10,020
If we go back, my grandma will find out,

228
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:12,440
and she definitely won't let me come out
to find my dad again.

229
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:15,300
Exactly. My dad definitely
won't let me come again.

230
00:09:15,510 --> 00:09:16,790
Just follow me.

231
00:09:19,090 --> 00:09:20,950
We'll rough it here for one night.

232
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:23,140
When it's light, we'll go find my dad.

233
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,480
If you don't want to go,

234
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,480
I'll go by myself.

235
00:09:25,780 --> 00:09:27,080
I need to ask him in person

236
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,320
why he abandoned me.

237
00:09:29,780 --> 00:09:30,690
Xiaoman!

238
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:32,080
Xiaoman, where are you?

239
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:32,720
Xiaoman!

240
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:33,750
Xia Lei, where are you?

241
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:34,600
Xiaoman!

242
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,790
Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

243
00:09:35,870 --> 00:09:36,680
Xiaodan!

244
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:38,550
Xiaoman!

245
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:39,630
Xiaodan!

246
00:09:39,650 --> 00:09:40,510
Xia Lei!

247
00:09:40,510 --> 00:09:41,840
Xiaoman!

248
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,510
-Xiaodan!
-Xia Lei!

249
00:09:43,510 --> 00:09:44,080
Xiaodan!

250
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,080
Xiaoman!

251
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:51,580
I wonder
how chaotic things are at home now.

252
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:54,610
My mom's gonna kill me when I get home.

253
00:09:55,670 --> 00:09:56,360
Xia Lei.

254
00:09:57,410 --> 00:09:59,070
I feel like I got you into this.

255
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,390
Why don't you just blame it on me?

256
00:10:01,390 --> 00:10:02,200
No way.

257
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:04,390
If I say that,

258
00:10:04,790 --> 00:10:06,150
chances are that my mom

259
00:10:06,150 --> 00:10:08,070
will never let me hang out
with you guys again.

260
00:10:08,070 --> 00:10:09,160
Then forget it.

261
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,000
Xia Lei, you're such a good student.

262
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,730
And your mom is still so strict.

263
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,550
Why do you always
want to hang out with us?

264
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:22,480
Because I think my mom
is more like a railway.

265
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,400
No matter how far I am from her,

266
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,900
she has everything arranged for me.

267
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:28,230
What are you guys doing?

268
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:30,070
Keep talking. I'm listening.

269
00:10:30,070 --> 00:10:30,870
Where were we?

270
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:32,840
Railway.

271
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:33,600
Right. Railway.

272
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:36,150
You guys are more like that arched bridge.

273
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:37,510
Hanging out with you,

274
00:10:37,510 --> 00:10:40,240
I always encounter
something magical, strange,

275
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:41,990
and unfamiliar.

276
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:44,000
I haven't really met your mother,

277
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:44,960
but when it comes to

278
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:46,750
arranging everything for others,

279
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,080
no one can beat my dad.

280
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:50,680
Every time he scolds me, he's like,

281
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:53,320
"You're a girl.
It's all for your own good."

282
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,380
You don't know how annoying my mom is.

283
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:57,670
Now that Xiaoman's seen her so many times,

284
00:10:57,670 --> 00:11:00,040
my mom doesn't even hold back
when she scolds me.

285
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:00,510
Xiaoman, where are you?

286
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:01,270
Xia Lei!

287
00:11:01,790 --> 00:11:02,670
Xiaodan!

288
00:11:02,670 --> 00:11:03,600
Shine the light up there.

289
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:04,320
Xia Lei!

290
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,860
Use that thing and wave it around.

291
00:11:05,860 --> 00:11:07,340
See if we can hear the kids.

292
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:08,600
These little rascals.

293
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,790
Xiaodan! Xiaoman!

294
00:11:09,790 --> 00:11:11,360
-Xiaoman!
-Have you found them?

295
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,080
No!

296
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:17,700
Xia Lei.

297
00:11:19,030 --> 00:11:20,750
Actually, when I was 6,

298
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,550
my mom left the factory.

299
00:11:23,430 --> 00:11:24,360
I've heard of it.

300
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,200
Most of the time, I blame my dad.

301
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,550
I think because of him,

302
00:11:30,610 --> 00:11:32,110
my mom left.

303
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,860
Sometimes, I blame my mom too.

304
00:11:36,370 --> 00:11:38,800
Is the outside world really so good

305
00:11:38,910 --> 00:11:41,970
that she had to see it
even if it meant leaving me behind?

306
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:50,870
Xiaoman.

307
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:54,600
Maybe

308
00:11:55,910 --> 00:11:57,970
your parents will come back someday.

309
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:00,230
Maybe they didn't abandon you.

310
00:12:00,230 --> 00:12:01,890
Actually, I blame myself too.

311
00:12:03,540 --> 00:12:05,200
Because I wasn't good enough,

312
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,240
they left me behind

313
00:12:08,390 --> 00:12:09,790
and left the factory.

314
00:12:14,030 --> 00:12:15,090
Stop crying first.

315
00:12:15,910 --> 00:12:17,960
I think you're not wrong, Xiaoman.

316
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:19,690
You have to trust me.

317
00:12:21,590 --> 00:12:23,920
You're actually right about some things.

318
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,910
Maybe your parents had no choice.

319
00:12:28,340 --> 00:12:31,000
Don't change yourself
because of other people.

320
00:12:31,610 --> 00:12:32,430
Don't cry.

321
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,870
Thank you, Xia Lei.

322
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,480
Let's be best friends forever.

323
00:12:38,590 --> 00:12:39,360
Forever.

324
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:58,280
Slow down. It's steep here.

325
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:08,010
How did we come here?

326
00:13:10,170 --> 00:13:12,430
Why are there so many graves on this hill?

327
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:14,150
This is the factory's public cemetery.

328
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:15,330
My grandfather is buried here.

329
00:13:15,330 --> 00:13:16,730
I know where to go now.

330
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:17,470
Follow me.

331
00:13:18,170 --> 00:13:19,240
This time, I believe you.

332
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:20,790
Who else would you believe if not me?

333
00:13:20,790 --> 00:13:21,670
We're here.

334
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:24,930
Look at you two. Like little mud monkeys.

335
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:27,280
Little spotted cat.

336
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:28,740
You have a painted face.

337
00:13:28,740 --> 00:13:30,000
-I'm not.
-You must be.

338
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:30,960
I'm Monkey Sun.

339
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:34,290
-The factory is starting to work!
-You are a monkey.

340
00:13:34,290 --> 00:13:39,390
♪ The five-star red flag
is flying in the wind ♪

341
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:40,550
Stop singing.

342
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:42,360
I need to wash my face.

343
00:13:42,670 --> 00:13:43,600
My grandma is very particular
about cleanliness.

344
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,240
If I don't wash up, she'll scold me.

345
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,840
Can't you wash up when we get back?

346
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,550
No. You guys go ahead.

347
00:13:49,030 --> 00:13:49,750
Hurry up.

348
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:57,390
Help me!

349
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:58,800
-Xiaoman!
-Xiaoman!

350
00:13:59,080 --> 00:13:59,870
Help me!

351
00:13:59,870 --> 00:14:00,480
Xiaoman!

352
00:14:00,710 --> 00:14:02,660
-Xiaoman! Xiaoman!
-Xiaoman!

353
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:06,440
-Xiaoman! Xiaoman!
-Xiaoman!

354
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:07,960
-Is anyone there?
-Is anyone there?

355
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,270
Someone is drowning!

356
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,790
Xiaoman!

357
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:14,270
Xiaoman!

358
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:16,230
Xiaoman!

359
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,670
Come here, Xiaoman!

360
00:14:17,670 --> 00:14:18,960
Someone help!

361
00:14:36,390 --> 00:14:36,790
Come!

362
00:14:36,990 --> 00:14:37,560
Xiaoman.

363
00:14:40,260 --> 00:14:40,790
Xiaoman.

364
00:14:42,060 --> 00:14:42,700
Xiaoman.

365
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:44,670
Xiaoman.

366
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,520
-Xiaoman.
-Xiaoman.

367
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:49,260
Go!

368
00:14:52,910 --> 00:14:53,930
Don't worry, Auntie.

369
00:14:53,930 --> 00:14:55,030
I've already talked to my wife about it.

370
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:56,960
She's been thinking about him too.

371
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,700
She's fond of this kid.

372
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,600
He'll be fine after getting some rest.

373
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,530
About this matter with his father,

374
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:03,480
don't overthink it.

375
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:04,840
Jiaming is such a scoundrel.

376
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,550
He forgets his mother
after getting married.

377
00:15:06,550 --> 00:15:07,630
The boy must have acted impulsively.

378
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:09,390
Grandma, is my dad back?

379
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,560
Grandma, is my dad back?

380
00:15:13,690 --> 00:15:14,410
He's awake.

381
00:15:16,210 --> 00:15:17,060
Uncle Ding.

382
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,240
I've already told your grandma.

383
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,580
From now on, come to me with any problems.

384
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:25,630
If you're bullied at school or anything,

385
00:15:25,630 --> 00:15:27,000
tell me directly, got it?

386
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:27,630
I got it.

387
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,920
Your grandfather and I were both soldiers.

388
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:31,630
Your father and I are fellow disciples.

389
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:32,510
No matter who else abandons you,

390
00:15:32,510 --> 00:15:33,860
I'll be there for you, understand?

391
00:15:33,860 --> 00:15:34,920
Yes, I understand.

392
00:15:37,310 --> 00:15:39,310
Come here. Let me feel your muscles.

393
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,360
This won't do.

394
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:42,620
Your build is too weak.

395
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:44,290
Too slight. You need to train.

396
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,030
Don't let him eat breakfast tomorrow,
Auntie.

397
00:15:46,030 --> 00:15:46,830
I understand.

398
00:15:46,850 --> 00:15:48,240
I'll wake him up early.

399
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:49,000
Good.

400
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:50,270
Stay with your grandma.

401
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:50,790
I'm heading back, Auntie.

402
00:15:50,790 --> 00:15:51,870
-Okay, Uncle Ding.
-Take care, Mr. Ding.

403
00:15:51,870 --> 00:15:52,750
Okay, okay.

404
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:54,840
The cart's back!

405
00:15:55,550 --> 00:15:56,440
Auntie, let me do it.

406
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:56,720
Auntie.

407
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:57,600
Don't bend over like that.

408
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,150
Your back can't take it.

409
00:15:58,150 --> 00:15:59,320
I oiled the wheels for you.

410
00:15:59,090 --> 00:16:02,990
♪ Smoke from the chimney drifted
back in those days ♪

411
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:00,510
It's much smoother now.

412
00:16:00,510 --> 00:16:02,910
Thank you, Xia, really.

413
00:16:03,150 --> 00:16:03,840
No problem. No problem.

414
00:16:03,390 --> 00:16:07,240
♪ Distant friends waving their hands ♪

415
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:05,000
-Let me push the cart.
-We're out of water too.

416
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,260
I'll go get some water.

417
00:16:06,510 --> 00:16:07,790
Are we missing some?

418
00:16:07,580 --> 00:16:11,470
♪ From some yard wall comes a whistle ♪

419
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:09,670
Going back and forth like this.

420
00:16:09,670 --> 00:16:11,530
Auntie, you brought vegetables.

421
00:16:11,550 --> 00:16:12,550
I'm going out for a bit.

422
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:15,750
♪ Blowing the years running along ♪

423
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:13,750
They need blanching.

424
00:16:13,790 --> 00:16:14,910
This one... That one...

425
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:15,600
Have you washed them?

426
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:16,550
They've been cut but not washed.

427
00:16:16,290 --> 00:16:20,250
♪ You're always on my mind ♪

428
00:16:16,550 --> 00:16:17,440
After you wash them...

429
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,150
I need to wash them.

430
00:16:18,150 --> 00:16:19,320
Blanch them in boiling water.

431
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,360
They're for a cold salad.

432
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:21,120
Cold salad.

433
00:16:20,450 --> 00:16:24,200
♪ How are you doing now? ♪

434
00:16:24,690 --> 00:16:28,740
♪ Would you know me when we meet again? ♪

435
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:25,670
Xia.

436
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:27,260
Much smoother now.

437
00:16:27,270 --> 00:16:28,470
Thanks for your help.

438
00:16:28,550 --> 00:16:29,510
If this gets stiff again,

439
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:33,090
♪ I grew tall through all the goodbyes ♪

440
00:16:29,510 --> 00:16:30,480
just let me know.

441
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:38,900
♪ The one who wept with longing ♪

442
00:16:39,070 --> 00:16:42,750
♪ Home is where your heart
stays attached ♪

443
00:16:43,380 --> 00:16:47,660
♪ Those cheeks flushed red in heavy snow ♪

444
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:51,660
♪ The smoke that rose to welcome me home ♪

445
00:16:52,220 --> 00:16:56,170
♪ The one I saw just by turning around ♪

446
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:59,820
♪ Home is where the door's left open
for me ♪

447
00:17:00,630 --> 00:17:04,920
♪ Trains keep rushing forward nonstop ♪

448
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:08,920
♪ But I go against the signs to find her ♪

449
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:07,510
Grandma.

450
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,200
I've washed the kelp.

451
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,339
It looks clear.

452
00:17:16,510 --> 00:17:17,510
You did a good job.

453
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:19,440
Here,

454
00:17:19,829 --> 00:17:20,960
have some cabbage hearts.

455
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:21,890
Cabbage hearts.

456
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:23,400
Thank you, Grandma.

457
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:30,000
Grandma, could you teach me
how to cut vegetables?

458
00:17:30,350 --> 00:17:31,220
Little dumpling,

459
00:17:31,220 --> 00:17:32,640
you can't even reach the stove.

460
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:35,030
Grandma, please teach me.

461
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:37,240
Alright then,

462
00:17:37,860 --> 00:17:39,420
I'll teach you.

463
00:17:39,830 --> 00:17:42,220
Cutting vegetables is a skilled craft.

464
00:17:43,550 --> 00:17:45,410
Use a straight knife for cabbage.

465
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,760
And a pulling motion, remember?

466
00:17:47,780 --> 00:17:49,030
After placing the straight knife here,

467
00:17:49,030 --> 00:17:50,890
you use a pulling motion for kelp.

468
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,030
Understand?

469
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:52,730
I got it.

470
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:56,420
Only when we are

471
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:57,760
clean and tidy

472
00:17:58,270 --> 00:18:00,830
will people trust our mixed dishes.

473
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:01,880
I understand, Grandma.

474
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,610
Give it to me.

475
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:03,720
I'll go get it.

476
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:05,680
When we're hygienic,

477
00:18:06,030 --> 00:18:07,590
people will trust you.

478
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:10,200
Good.

479
00:18:11,110 --> 00:18:11,830
Close the door.

480
00:18:11,830 --> 00:18:12,440
Okay.

481
00:18:13,460 --> 00:18:14,010
Alright.

482
00:18:14,110 --> 00:18:14,710
Come here.

483
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:16,580
Let me take a look at you.

484
00:18:17,070 --> 00:18:18,200
Look at my grandson.

485
00:18:20,350 --> 00:18:21,550
So neat and tidy.

486
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:23,410
Looking great.

487
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:24,920
Let's go.

488
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:25,580
Let's move!

489
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:29,510
One, two, three, go!

490
00:18:29,510 --> 00:18:31,160
Alright, we're going.

491
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:35,990
Turn.

492
00:18:37,530 --> 00:18:38,310
Slow down, Grandma.

493
00:18:38,310 --> 00:18:39,160
Alright.

494
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:52,330
[1996]

495
00:18:51,550 --> 00:18:52,860
-Which one do you want?
-Almost.

496
00:18:52,860 --> 00:18:53,350
Xia Lei.

497
00:18:53,350 --> 00:18:54,410
This one, this one.

498
00:18:54,590 --> 00:18:55,640
Let me see how much it costs.

499
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,680
Let me take a look first.

500
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:57,510
Okay, okay.

501
00:18:58,070 --> 00:18:58,480
Let me have a sip.

502
00:18:58,480 --> 00:18:59,480
Go ahead and look.

503
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:01,170
It's so sour.

504
00:19:02,890 --> 00:19:05,810
A train bound for Shenzhen
from Beijing West...

505
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:07,170
Put it over there for me.

506
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:08,270
Alright.

507
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:10,110
Under the watchful eyes of thousands,

508
00:19:10,110 --> 00:19:13,550
it slowly departs from
the Beijing West Railway Station platform.

509
00:19:13,550 --> 00:19:14,550
This moment

510
00:19:14,790 --> 00:19:18,510
marks the full opening

511
00:19:18,530 --> 00:19:19,880
of the Beijing-Kowloon Railway—

512
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:21,510
-OK. Take it.
-Come again.

513
00:19:21,510 --> 00:19:22,030
Sure.

514
00:19:22,510 --> 00:19:24,240
China's biggest and most heavily-invested

515
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:26,830
railway project ever.

516
00:19:27,970 --> 00:19:29,130
Alright, that's enough.

517
00:19:29,130 --> 00:19:30,530
What are you waiting for?

518
00:19:31,140 --> 00:19:32,110
Xiaoman,

519
00:19:32,710 --> 00:19:35,210
go to school with Lei.

520
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:37,060
Well...

521
00:19:37,790 --> 00:19:39,880
I can handle the rest of the work myself.

522
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,180
-We'll make it in time.
-We won't be delayed.

523
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:42,750
-No way.
-We won't be delayed.

524
00:19:42,750 --> 00:19:44,550
Today is the first day of school.

525
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:47,100
It would be terrible to be late.
Listen to me.

526
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:47,600
I know.

527
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:48,350
Hurry up.

528
00:19:48,350 --> 00:19:49,180
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

529
00:19:49,180 --> 00:19:50,940
Drink up.
Put the bottle here when you're done.

530
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:52,070
Put the bottle here.

531
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:52,960
We're leaving, Grandma.

532
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:54,090
Ma'am, we're going.

533
00:19:55,140 --> 00:19:55,530
Go.

534
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:56,800
Slow down. Slow down.

535
00:19:57,130 --> 00:19:58,760
Go. Hurry up.

536
00:19:59,160 --> 00:19:59,790
Go for it.

537
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:03,350
These two kids have grown up so fast.

538
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:06,310
[Western Tiecheng
Dongfang Affiliated Middle School]

539
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:13,450
The holiday is gone again.

540
00:20:14,310 --> 00:20:15,480
Xiaoman, Xia Lei!

541
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,440
Dongdong.

542
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:19,350
Have you guys noticed?

543
00:20:19,350 --> 00:20:19,790
What's up, Dongdong?

544
00:20:19,790 --> 00:20:22,000
Girls really change as they grow up.

545
00:20:22,310 --> 00:20:24,550
I was watching
at the school gate for a while.

546
00:20:24,550 --> 00:20:26,510
All the girls at our school have changed.

547
00:20:26,510 --> 00:20:27,200
How so?

548
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:28,860
They care about their appearance now.

549
00:20:28,860 --> 00:20:30,350
They've all dolled themselves up

550
00:20:30,350 --> 00:20:31,410
and look so pretty.

551
00:20:31,510 --> 00:20:32,440
I don't think so.

552
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:33,470
Look, look.

553
00:20:34,310 --> 00:20:35,790
No wonder she's from the big city.

554
00:20:35,790 --> 00:20:36,750
Those white sneakers.

555
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:38,310
-Yeah.
-They look expensive.

556
00:20:38,310 --> 00:20:40,510
They definitely look better than ours.

557
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:42,270
Xiaoman, Xia Lei!

558
00:20:43,310 --> 00:20:44,270
Wait for me!

559
00:20:45,030 --> 00:20:45,590
Let's go.

560
00:20:46,750 --> 00:20:47,030
You just got here.

561
00:20:47,030 --> 00:20:48,830
What's going on? Why didn't you call me?

562
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:51,030
I was helping my grandma with her stall.

563
00:20:51,590 --> 00:20:52,450
What about you?

564
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:54,820
I-I was picking up Xiaoman.

565
00:20:55,110 --> 00:20:55,640
Xiaodan.

566
00:20:55,660 --> 00:20:57,860
-I just...
-It's none of your business.

567
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:01,160
Fine, fine.

568
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,220
I forgive you guys.

569
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:05,730
By the way, Xiaoman.

570
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:07,880
Today we're selecting class officers.

571
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:08,550
My mom said

572
00:21:08,550 --> 00:21:10,420
it might be related
to future college recommendations.

573
00:21:10,420 --> 00:21:11,880
That'll be no problem for you.

574
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:14,370
Your grades are top in our year, right?

575
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,650
You'll definitely be the class president.

576
00:21:15,650 --> 00:21:16,510
We must vote for him.

577
00:21:16,510 --> 00:21:17,640
I'll help campaign for you. Don't worry.

578
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:19,370
-I vote for you too.
-Thank you.

579
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:20,310
Hey.

580
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:23,180
-What are you doing?
-What are you doing?

581
00:21:23,590 --> 00:21:24,960
Don't you know you were blocking my way?

582
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:25,510
Forget it.

583
00:21:25,510 --> 00:21:26,510
But you can't just hit people.

584
00:21:26,510 --> 00:21:27,200
The road is so wide,

585
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:29,130
but you had to squeeze in behind me.

586
00:21:30,230 --> 00:21:32,230
What? What's that supposed to mean?

587
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:33,830
Forget it. Forget it.

588
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:34,880
No, it's nothing, Bo.

589
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:36,200
Forget it? No way.

590
00:21:36,910 --> 00:21:37,720
Just messing around.

591
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:38,500
It's nothing, Bo.

592
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:39,060
Nothing?

593
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:39,760
Nothing.

594
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:41,650
Watch yourselves.

595
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:45,160
What's wrong with that guy?

596
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:45,920
Watch ourselves?

597
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:47,070
Just because he's in a higher grade,

598
00:21:47,070 --> 00:21:49,030
he always bullies those younger than him.

599
00:21:49,030 --> 00:21:50,030
Don't be like him.

600
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:51,240
What a real achiever.

601
00:21:51,790 --> 00:21:52,320
Let's go.

602
00:21:52,790 --> 00:21:54,160
-Let's go!
-My jacket!

603
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:55,490
Go home and get changed.

604
00:21:55,490 --> 00:21:56,310
It's expensive!

605
00:21:56,310 --> 00:21:57,270
Look at you!

606
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:58,750
Don't tear it!

607
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:00,680
Are you trying to be a wheeler-dealer?

608
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:02,340
Hurry up and go home to change!

609
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:05,400
Isn't that Zhuang Sen?

610
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:06,200
Go change.

611
00:22:07,270 --> 00:22:10,000
Nothing in the school rule says
I can't wear this.

612
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:13,330
You're so annoying!

613
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:14,880
He's running away!

614
00:22:16,070 --> 00:22:17,030
I'll expel you!

615
00:22:17,150 --> 00:22:18,460
I don't care!

616
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:21,590
I...

617
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:25,090
Zhuang Sen is truly
our factory's most fashionable guy.

618
00:22:25,090 --> 00:22:25,600
Class is starting. Let's go.

619
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:26,830
He's quite fluent in English.

620
00:22:26,830 --> 00:22:28,240
"I don't..." How did he say it?

621
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:29,480
"I don't care."

622
00:22:32,790 --> 00:22:33,450
Quiet down!

623
00:22:39,790 --> 00:22:42,830
[Tong Yue'e]

624
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,200
Hello, everyone.

625
00:22:46,870 --> 00:22:49,800
I'll be your homeroom teacher
for the next two years.

626
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,790
Just call me Ms. Tong.

627
00:22:52,510 --> 00:22:55,830
I'll help you get fully prepared
for the college entrance exam.

628
00:22:55,830 --> 00:22:56,480
Bravo!

629
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:58,090
Hello, Ms. Tong.

630
00:22:59,350 --> 00:22:59,960
Alright.

631
00:23:00,350 --> 00:23:03,500
First, I'd like to introduce a new student
to you.

632
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:07,830
She's Meng Ge, transferred from Beijing.

633
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:11,610
Hello everyone, I'm Meng Ge.

634
00:23:11,750 --> 00:23:13,750
It's a real pleasure
to be in the same class as you.

635
00:23:13,750 --> 00:23:14,950
Hope we'll get along.

636
00:23:19,230 --> 00:23:22,560
You've all seen the seating chart
on the blackboard, right?

637
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:24,050
This seating arrangement

638
00:23:24,050 --> 00:23:25,380
was made based on

639
00:23:26,030 --> 00:23:28,030
your Grade 10 final exam results,

640
00:23:28,030 --> 00:23:29,980
your height, and eyesight.

641
00:23:30,380 --> 00:23:32,570
For those sitting in the back,
don't be discouraged.

642
00:23:32,570 --> 00:23:33,500
The chart

643
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:36,030
will be adjusted
according to your performance

644
00:23:36,030 --> 00:23:37,350
in each monthly exam.

645
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:38,920
As students,

646
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:41,810
your positions can be changed
through study.

647
00:23:42,410 --> 00:23:44,720
When you leave school
and step into the real world,

648
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:46,980
you'll understand that all good results

649
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,130
come from hard work.

650
00:23:48,790 --> 00:23:49,400
Alright.

651
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:53,790
Next, let's select class representatives.

652
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:57,920
Today, I'll appoint

653
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:59,270
certain students

654
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:01,000
based on my knowledge of you.

655
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:03,830
Should you have complaints about them
in the future,

656
00:24:03,830 --> 00:24:05,290
we'll hold a new election.

657
00:24:06,030 --> 00:24:07,400
I've picked Xia Lei,

658
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:10,370
since he ranked first
in the previous grade exam.

659
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:19,760
Yan Xiaodan, a versatile fellow of yours,
is chosen as well,

660
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:27,090
together with Meng Ge,

661
00:24:27,150 --> 00:24:30,250
a well-rounded student new to our class.

662
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,830
They will each be assigned

663
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:37,650
different responsibilities.

664
00:24:45,070 --> 00:24:45,960
You're back, Lei.

665
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:46,640
Hello, sir.

666
00:24:47,880 --> 00:24:48,510
Honey!

667
00:24:49,960 --> 00:24:51,640
Where's the vinegar I just bought?

668
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:52,920
Right on the counter.

669
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:53,720
I didn't move it.

670
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:54,980
Where did you place it?

671
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:56,550
Gosh.

672
00:24:56,550 --> 00:24:57,590
Come help me find it.

673
00:24:57,590 --> 00:24:59,790
What are your eyes for, eating noodles?

674
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:01,070
Hurry up. I need it right now.

675
00:25:01,070 --> 00:25:01,870
Welcome back.

676
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:09,310
Good to see you back, Lei.

677
00:25:09,310 --> 00:25:10,640
Did you even look for it?

678
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:13,910
Lei, we're having chicken drumsticks
for dinner!

679
00:25:19,550 --> 00:25:20,750
He's not responding.

680
00:25:21,510 --> 00:25:22,910
Cover for me and stir fry.

681
00:25:26,270 --> 00:25:28,870
Lei, I'm serving chicken drumsticks
tonight.

682
00:25:28,940 --> 00:25:30,460
Yes, I heard you.

683
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,650
Our son seems to be in a bad mood.

684
00:25:38,950 --> 00:25:39,810
Go check on him.

685
00:25:40,090 --> 00:25:40,760
He's fine.

686
00:25:41,250 --> 00:25:42,380
Just go check on him.

687
00:25:43,110 --> 00:25:44,060
Hurry.

688
00:25:45,110 --> 00:25:45,920
Son.

689
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:47,790
What happened?

690
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:50,030
I didn't get to be

691
00:25:50,550 --> 00:25:52,660
the class president or the study monitor.

692
00:25:52,660 --> 00:25:54,960
I only ended up
being the sanitation monitor.

693
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:56,360
Sounds like a decent job.

694
00:25:57,830 --> 00:25:58,920
At least it means you've got

695
00:25:58,920 --> 00:26:00,790
the teacher's attention, right?

696
00:26:01,110 --> 00:26:03,680
The study monitor's grades
aren't even as good as mine,

697
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:07,080
but she still got the job
because her father is Director Meng.

698
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:08,920
I'm telling you, Son,

699
00:26:09,350 --> 00:26:11,550
everyone has to walk his or her own path.

700
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:12,960
It seems opaque at young ages,

701
00:26:12,960 --> 00:26:14,160
but all becomes clear

702
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:16,140
when you grow into adults.

703
00:26:16,160 --> 00:26:18,550
One's life is built
through his or her own efforts.

704
00:26:18,550 --> 00:26:21,030
Perhaps you do outperform
the study monitor academically,

705
00:26:21,030 --> 00:26:22,400
but she's more sophisticated.

706
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:23,480
Here's an analogy.

707
00:26:23,590 --> 00:26:25,480
On a rainy day,

708
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:27,680
everyone's waiting at the same bus stop

709
00:26:27,740 --> 00:26:29,670
probably for different vehicles.

710
00:26:29,760 --> 00:26:31,550
Some people are waiting for private cars

711
00:26:31,550 --> 00:26:32,680
that quickly arrive

712
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:33,480
and pick them up.

713
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:35,640
Others are waiting for buses.

714
00:26:35,790 --> 00:26:37,510
The wait could be long,

715
00:26:37,790 --> 00:26:39,240
and the ride may be rough.

716
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:41,350
With luck, they might meet up again
down the road.

717
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:42,070
But some others

718
00:26:42,070 --> 00:26:43,510
can't even get on a bus.

719
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:46,790
Such is the gap
that separates one person from another.

720
00:26:46,790 --> 00:26:48,320
If you are to narrow the gap,

721
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,640
you need to work hard.

722
00:26:51,510 --> 00:26:52,310
What's wrong?

723
00:26:54,110 --> 00:26:55,200
Don't be disheartened.

724
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:57,660
Our family's neither the best
nor the worst.

725
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:58,310
For what it's worth,

726
00:26:58,310 --> 00:26:59,590
your father and I are able

727
00:26:59,590 --> 00:27:00,830
to provide you with a proper environment

728
00:27:00,830 --> 00:27:02,090
where you can study without worries.

729
00:27:02,090 --> 00:27:04,070
Son, just stay down-to-earth

730
00:27:04,070 --> 00:27:05,270
and study hard.

731
00:27:05,590 --> 00:27:08,400
Good grades will bring you
good opportunities, right?

732
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:10,330
Then you'll get to create a new life

733
00:27:10,390 --> 00:27:11,990
and reach a higher position.

734
00:27:13,030 --> 00:27:15,290
I just hope you won't end up
like your dad and me.

735
00:27:15,290 --> 00:27:15,940
You see,

736
00:27:16,230 --> 00:27:19,480
we've spent our entire lives
working in the East Chemical Plant.

737
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:20,640
Yes, don't be like us.

738
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:21,590
I agree with your mother.

739
00:27:21,590 --> 00:27:22,110
Son,

740
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:24,480
as long as you remain
the top student of your school,

741
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:25,070
you'll practically

742
00:27:25,070 --> 00:27:27,630
have a foot in
one of the most prestigious universities

743
00:27:27,630 --> 00:27:29,020
in Beijing

744
00:27:30,310 --> 00:27:31,480
or Shanghai.

745
00:27:32,060 --> 00:27:33,140
A-Am I saying it

746
00:27:33,250 --> 00:27:34,340
wrong?

747
00:27:34,690 --> 00:27:36,450
No. You're making perfect sense.
Why the smirk?

748
00:27:36,450 --> 00:27:37,750
I'm picturing something funny.

749
00:27:37,750 --> 00:27:39,070
If one foot is in Beijing,

750
00:27:39,070 --> 00:27:40,240
and the other in Shanghai,

751
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:42,110
h-his two legs will be so widely

752
00:27:42,110 --> 00:27:44,260
stretched apart
that his groin might get hurt.

753
00:27:44,260 --> 00:27:45,430
Stop rambling on.

754
00:27:45,750 --> 00:27:46,640
That's a real risk.

755
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:47,970
Your mom doesn't get it.

756
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:49,030
Alright then.

757
00:27:49,030 --> 00:27:51,000
Help me set up the table now.

758
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:52,400
Come on. Dinner's ready.

759
00:27:52,610 --> 00:27:53,760
Hurry up.

760
00:27:54,310 --> 00:27:55,640
You should come out too.

761
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,030
Have dinner before eating fruit.

762
00:27:57,030 --> 00:27:58,270
Come on.

763
00:27:58,270 --> 00:27:59,800
Have you washed your hands?

764
00:27:59,830 --> 00:28:00,400
-Not yet.
-Be quick!

765
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:01,730
Set up the table with me.

766
00:28:01,850 --> 00:28:02,930
Can't you straighten your back?

767
00:28:02,930 --> 00:28:04,990
Slouching like a shrimp all the time.

768
00:28:06,110 --> 00:28:07,400
Xiaoman, why the rush?

769
00:28:07,750 --> 00:28:09,680
Do you know how much
Xiaoman's grandma loves him?

770
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:10,310
How much?

771
00:28:10,310 --> 00:28:11,310
She gives him
as much allowance as he wants.

772
00:28:11,310 --> 00:28:12,110
Seriously?

773
00:28:12,750 --> 00:28:13,920
His grandma really dotes on him.

774
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:14,720
Indeed.

775
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:15,680
After all, both his parents passed away,

776
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:17,310
and he is the only family she's got.

777
00:28:17,310 --> 00:28:18,840
Hurry. The bell's ringing.

778
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,310
Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

779
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:24,950
Come over!

780
00:28:25,070 --> 00:28:25,600
For what?

781
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:26,320
Just come.

782
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,800
I wonder what's going on.

783
00:28:31,030 --> 00:28:31,630
What's up?

784
00:28:32,110 --> 00:28:33,440
Xiaobo wants to see you.

785
00:28:34,510 --> 00:28:35,570
What's the matter?

786
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,270
Would you lend me 100 yuan?

787
00:28:37,270 --> 00:28:37,920
How much?

788
00:28:38,590 --> 00:28:39,550
One hundred?

789
00:28:40,350 --> 00:28:41,880
I doubt if my family's stall
is even worth 100 yuan.

790
00:28:41,880 --> 00:28:43,070
How am I supposed to lend you that much?

791
00:28:43,070 --> 00:28:44,070
Ask your grandma for it.

792
00:28:44,070 --> 00:28:45,270
Doesn't she love you?

793
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,110
You can steal, rob, or borrow.

794
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:48,240
Do whatever you can.

795
00:28:48,950 --> 00:28:51,200
My grandma can't give me that much money,

796
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,330
though she loves me.

797
00:28:52,590 --> 00:28:53,680
Besides, honestly,

798
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:55,590
there isn't even 100 yuan
at home for me to steal.

799
00:28:55,590 --> 00:28:56,440
Why do you ask me for it?

800
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:57,880
You should borrow from someone else.

801
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:59,610
I insist on borrowing from you,

802
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:01,080
since you're a pushover.

803
00:29:01,270 --> 00:29:02,750
All the other students have parents.

804
00:29:02,750 --> 00:29:03,790
But what about you?

805
00:29:03,790 --> 00:29:05,480
Your family runs a lowly street stall.

806
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:07,540
Who else am I going to bully if not you?

807
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:11,400
Well...

808
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,570
Buddy, how about this?

809
00:29:16,340 --> 00:29:19,310
My family's newsstand just bought
a batch of old books

810
00:29:19,310 --> 00:29:20,770
from the factory library.

811
00:29:21,590 --> 00:29:22,830
I'll get you one.

812
00:29:24,170 --> 00:29:24,770
What book?

813
00:29:25,160 --> 00:29:26,550
Guidance for the Newlyweds.

814
00:29:26,550 --> 00:29:27,550
I'm not getting married.

815
00:29:27,550 --> 00:29:28,590
Why would I need it?

816
00:29:28,590 --> 00:29:29,110
Xiaobo,

817
00:29:29,350 --> 00:29:30,480
that book comes with

818
00:29:30,770 --> 00:29:31,440
pictures.

819
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:36,680
Pictures?

820
00:29:37,590 --> 00:29:38,650
Colored pictures.

821
00:29:40,770 --> 00:29:41,720
Bring it to me tomorrow.

822
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:42,240
Sure.

823
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:43,320
No problem.

824
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:44,270
I'll bring it to you tomorrow.

825
00:29:44,270 --> 00:29:45,000
I'm leaving.

826
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,490
Don't forget that 100 yuan!

827
00:29:52,710 --> 00:29:53,230
Okay.

828
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:59,200
What did Feng Xiaobo want with you?

829
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:00,800
Nothing. Just a random chat.

830
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:03,480
Word has it that he often extorts
students in lower grades for money.

831
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:04,550
Let me know if he bullies you.

832
00:30:04,550 --> 00:30:05,590
I'll have my brother beat him up.

833
00:30:05,590 --> 00:30:06,480
No need.

834
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,400
He should be glad that I don't

835
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:08,820
bully him, that tiny little thing.

836
00:30:08,820 --> 00:30:10,820
Then what did he chat with you about?

837
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:14,160
He asked for some nice books
from my family's newsstand.

838
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:15,710
What nice books could

839
00:30:15,710 --> 00:30:16,880
someone like him be into?

840
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:17,640
Yeah.

841
00:30:18,240 --> 00:30:19,300
Just "nice" books.

842
00:30:21,070 --> 00:30:22,590
Good for him.

843
00:30:22,830 --> 00:30:23,870
D-Do you have any of those?

844
00:30:23,870 --> 00:30:24,600
You want one?

845
00:30:25,640 --> 00:30:26,400
Come on. Time to go home.

846
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:26,930
Let's go.

847
00:30:30,500 --> 00:30:32,200
"Nice" books indeed.

848
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:37,030
Grandma!

849
00:30:37,130 --> 00:30:38,830
-Let me do it. It’s raining.
-You’re back.

850
00:30:38,830 --> 00:30:39,750
It's raining. Hurry.

851
00:30:39,750 --> 00:30:40,240
Let me do it.

852
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:41,240
Pack up the stuff.

853
00:30:41,640 --> 00:30:43,230
I'll finish this up.

854
00:30:44,720 --> 00:30:45,960
Xia Lei, hurry. It's raining.

855
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:46,920
Grandma, don't stay outside.

856
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:48,610
-It’s raining.
-Grandma, don’t get wet.

857
00:30:48,610 --> 00:30:49,960
Be quick with the packing.

858
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:52,070
Alright. I'll go home
to make you stewed beans.

859
00:30:52,070 --> 00:30:52,590
Okay.

860
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:54,940
-You go home first, Grandma.
-Take care.

861
00:30:56,590 --> 00:30:58,110
Where did I put it?

862
00:30:58,760 --> 00:30:59,820
What are you doing?

863
00:31:00,830 --> 00:31:01,510
Looking for something.

864
00:31:01,510 --> 00:31:02,970
I'm back for the money box.

865
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:04,720
Grandma, stay out of the rain.

866
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:05,480
Go home now.

867
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:07,540
It's raining. Had better leave soon.

868
00:31:16,640 --> 00:31:18,170
Are you not done with it yet?

869
00:31:18,450 --> 00:31:19,400
I'm waiting for you.

870
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:20,030
Why?

871
00:31:20,030 --> 00:31:20,890
Just go home.

872
00:31:21,030 --> 00:31:22,790
I can't walk that far without your help.

873
00:31:22,790 --> 00:31:23,920
Okay. I'll be right with you.

874
00:31:23,920 --> 00:31:24,960
Be quick. It's raining.

875
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:25,890
I found it. I did.

876
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:27,510
Get out of the rain,

877
00:31:28,310 --> 00:31:28,840
Grandma.

878
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:31,790
I'm fine. It's just a drizzle.

879
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:39,130
Xiaoman, hurry up!

880
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:40,770
It's going to pour soon.

881
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:41,690
Let's go.

882
00:31:42,270 --> 00:31:43,400
I'll close the door.

883
00:31:57,890 --> 00:31:59,620
Lei, it's time to go to bed.

884
00:31:59,650 --> 00:32:00,510
Stop studying.

885
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,330
Yes, right away!

886
00:32:06,350 --> 00:32:06,880
Xiaoman.

887
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:09,930
Be quick.
I'll wait for you at the school gate.

888
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:16,000
There you are.

889
00:32:16,710 --> 00:32:17,770
Where's the stuff?

890
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:18,680
Right here.

891
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:26,640
What about the money?

892
00:32:26,830 --> 00:32:27,640
That... I

893
00:32:28,590 --> 00:32:29,250
don't have.

894
00:32:29,970 --> 00:32:30,570
You don't?

895
00:32:31,310 --> 00:32:32,640
Are you messing with me?

896
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:33,960
-Well...
-Don't get physical.

897
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:34,830
I've got money on me.

898
00:32:34,830 --> 00:32:35,920
You stay out of it.

899
00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:36,640
Get in the room.

900
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,440
This is none of your business.

901
00:32:37,440 --> 00:32:38,030
What do you mean?

902
00:32:38,030 --> 00:32:38,720
You want to die or what?

903
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:39,270
No, no, no.

904
00:32:39,270 --> 00:32:40,310
P-P-Please don't hurt me.

905
00:32:40,310 --> 00:32:41,000
I'll get you the money.

906
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,030
I-I brought it here.

907
00:32:42,030 --> 00:32:43,960
Let me get it for you. Just a second.

908
00:32:43,960 --> 00:32:44,760
Give him mine.

909
00:32:46,270 --> 00:32:47,030
Wait. What are you doing?

910
00:32:47,030 --> 00:32:48,690
Why not just give him my money?

911
00:32:48,790 --> 00:32:50,250
I bet you have a death wish!

912
00:32:50,250 --> 00:32:51,250
Stop right there!

913
00:32:51,270 --> 00:32:52,330
Don't you dare run!

914
00:32:53,310 --> 00:32:54,710
-Stop!
-What's going on?

915
00:32:55,830 --> 00:32:56,890
Stay where you are!

916
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:57,760
Stop running!

917
00:32:58,030 --> 00:32:59,070
I'll crush you!

918
00:32:59,130 --> 00:33:00,070
Stop right there!

919
00:33:00,070 --> 00:33:00,640
Run, huh?

920
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:02,310
Let's talk this through.

921
00:33:02,310 --> 00:33:03,370
Talk this through?

922
00:33:03,430 --> 00:33:04,630
Will you even listen?

923
00:33:05,310 --> 00:33:05,790
I will.

924
00:33:05,790 --> 00:33:07,320
Did I not talk nicely to you?

925
00:33:07,790 --> 00:33:08,680
Did you listen?

926
00:33:09,710 --> 00:33:10,970
Don't come any closer.

927
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:12,080
Or I'll jump.

928
00:33:12,510 --> 00:33:13,270
You'll jump?

929
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:15,830
Okay. Do it now.

930
00:33:16,290 --> 00:33:17,420
Jump. I'm watching.

931
00:33:19,760 --> 00:33:21,040
Jump, now!

932
00:33:21,590 --> 00:33:22,650
I just recalled it.

933
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:24,600
You should call me Uncle.

934
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:26,320
We're actually related.

935
00:33:26,550 --> 00:33:27,440
And I'll say I'm your dad's brother.

936
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,200
Related? What a lame excuse.

937
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:29,200
No, I mean it.

938
00:33:29,830 --> 00:33:30,830
My second uncle's

939
00:33:31,070 --> 00:33:34,270
daughter-in-law's brother's mother-in-law
is your great-aunt.

940
00:33:34,270 --> 00:33:35,240
What's this noise about?

941
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:36,350
Feng Xiaobo is in trouble.

942
00:33:36,350 --> 00:33:37,530
He extorted Xiaoman and ended up

943
00:33:37,530 --> 00:33:38,550
being beaten.

944
00:33:43,050 --> 00:33:43,640
Make way!

945
00:33:43,640 --> 00:33:44,700
Let me get through!

946
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:47,070
Is that so?

947
00:33:47,070 --> 00:33:47,440
Yes!

948
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:48,680
We're relatives, aren't we?

949
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:49,640
You mean my great-aunt...

950
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:50,030
Right.

951
00:33:50,030 --> 00:33:51,400
You big liar!

952
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:51,790
I'm serious...

953
00:33:51,790 --> 00:33:53,720
Don't you mess with Xiaoman again!

954
00:33:56,590 --> 00:33:57,720
You'll pay for this!

955
00:33:58,310 --> 00:33:59,400
Shut up!

956
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:01,310
Why did you do that?

957
00:34:01,310 --> 00:34:02,590
Because he bullied you.

958
00:34:02,590 --> 00:34:03,980
But... My goodness.

959
00:34:05,430 --> 00:34:06,430
Wait and see!

960
00:34:07,270 --> 00:34:08,510
The water splashed on me.

961
00:34:08,510 --> 00:34:09,570
How dare you laugh?

962
00:34:10,139 --> 00:34:11,449
Why didn't you fight him?

963
00:34:11,449 --> 00:34:13,710
Feng Xiaobo was already cornered
like a rat.

964
00:34:13,710 --> 00:34:15,000
I didn't get a chance to fight him.

965
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:15,730
Are you okay?

966
00:34:18,550 --> 00:34:19,860
You're really something.

967
00:34:19,860 --> 00:34:21,030
And why are you this happy?

968
00:34:21,030 --> 00:34:23,159
Why didn't you tell us he picked on you?

969
00:34:23,280 --> 00:34:24,880
It was not worth mentioning.

970
00:34:25,219 --> 00:34:27,219
The problem has gone with the water.

971
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:29,070
Don't you hide

972
00:34:29,070 --> 00:34:30,190
anything from us again.

973
00:34:30,190 --> 00:34:31,790
Just tell us if you need help.

974
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:34,110
Are you still confused
about what happened?

975
00:34:34,110 --> 00:34:35,440
What exactly happened?

976
00:34:35,510 --> 00:34:36,510
Impressive, Xiaodan.

977
00:34:36,510 --> 00:34:37,800
You're a true heroine.

978
00:34:45,510 --> 00:34:46,110
Grandma!

979
00:34:47,070 --> 00:34:48,400
I'm home.

980
00:34:50,150 --> 00:34:51,880
We're having dumplings today?

981
00:34:52,710 --> 00:34:53,510
Let me help.

982
00:34:56,550 --> 00:34:57,750
Pickled vegetables.

983
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:00,860
Put more meat in, Grandma.

984
00:35:04,990 --> 00:35:06,920
Do you know what you've done?

985
00:35:12,150 --> 00:35:14,510
What have I done?
I'm just back from school.

986
00:35:14,510 --> 00:35:15,320
Confess now!

987
00:35:15,550 --> 00:35:16,650
You attacked someone!

988
00:35:16,650 --> 00:35:17,530
What's the matter, Grandma?

989
00:35:17,530 --> 00:35:18,860
Who taught you all that?

990
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:21,280
Since when have you become like this?

991
00:35:21,280 --> 00:35:22,110
Like what?

992
00:35:22,110 --> 00:35:23,580
You hit someone with a bat today.

993
00:35:23,580 --> 00:35:25,360
Will you wield a knife tomorrow?

994
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:26,510
Grandma, ignore those rumors.

995
00:35:26,510 --> 00:35:28,240
Feng Xiaobo is a troublemaker.

996
00:35:29,450 --> 00:35:30,780
He's a troublemaker...

997
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:32,360
Come over here!

998
00:35:33,230 --> 00:35:34,800
Can it justify your use of violence?

999
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:36,510
Are you expecting me, an old woman,

1000
00:35:36,510 --> 00:35:38,970
to bail you out of police detention
someday?

1001
00:35:39,030 --> 00:35:39,630
No.

1002
00:35:39,670 --> 00:35:41,510
Grandma, d-don't be mad.

1003
00:35:41,670 --> 00:35:42,510
Don't listen to their nonsense.

1004
00:35:42,510 --> 00:35:43,920
I won't do it again. I know I was wrong.

1005
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:45,120
You won't do it again?

1006
00:35:48,850 --> 00:35:49,690
Xiaoman,

1007
00:35:51,190 --> 00:35:52,590
young trees

1008
00:35:53,630 --> 00:35:55,760
won't grow straight without pruning.

1009
00:35:56,630 --> 00:35:58,490
The same applies to young people.

1010
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:01,240
Growing slowly is not a problem,

1011
00:36:01,920 --> 00:36:04,030
but growing crooked is.

1012
00:36:05,870 --> 00:36:07,910
Grandma, don't worry.

1013
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:09,760
I assure you I won't grow crooked.

1014
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:11,880
If you ever find me growing the wrong way,

1015
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:12,840
discipline me immediately,

1016
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:14,440
beat me up, and reprimand me.

1017
00:36:18,110 --> 00:36:19,590
Grandma, I know you're the best.

1018
00:36:19,590 --> 00:36:21,360
Grandma, p-please stop being mad.

1019
00:36:21,360 --> 00:36:22,220
Don't be upset.

1020
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:23,480
I-I won't make the same mistake.

1021
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:24,810
Just don't worry, okay?

1022
00:36:25,190 --> 00:36:26,590
Let's make dumplings and cook.

1023
00:36:26,590 --> 00:36:27,400
I'm starving.

1024
00:36:30,370 --> 00:36:31,480
Grandma, rest assured.

1025
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:32,920
Please don't be mad.

1026
00:36:32,940 --> 00:36:33,980
Alright. Fine.

1027
00:36:34,030 --> 00:36:34,840
I got it.

1028
00:36:36,070 --> 00:36:37,280
I'll roll the dough.

1029
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:41,710
Actually,

1030
00:36:42,250 --> 00:36:45,930
it's a good thing that you have the guts
to stand up to bullies.

1031
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:49,070
Children of the Zhang family

1032
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:51,670
must not be bullied by anyone.

1033
00:36:52,510 --> 00:36:53,920
A man shouldn't

1034
00:36:54,790 --> 00:36:58,060
prove his worth with his fists,

1035
00:36:59,590 --> 00:37:01,280
but with his wits.

1036
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:02,670
Got it?

1037
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:05,070
Got it.

1038
00:37:06,030 --> 00:37:06,840
I understand.

1039
00:37:08,840 --> 00:37:10,590
Let's make dumplings and cook.

1040
00:37:14,540 --> 00:37:17,660
This year's school variety show
will commence soon.

1041
00:37:18,510 --> 00:37:19,910
Given the tight schedule

1042
00:37:20,030 --> 00:37:20,920
of grade 12 students,

1043
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:23,190
the task to perform has fallen on those
in 10th and 11th grades.

1044
00:37:23,190 --> 00:37:24,190
Our class needs to

1045
00:37:24,230 --> 00:37:25,430
put on a performance.

1046
00:37:25,550 --> 00:37:26,760
I've decided for you.

1047
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:28,280
Just like when class representatives
were selected,

1048
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:30,010
those two will be chosen again.

1049
00:37:32,320 --> 00:37:32,960
Xia Lei,

1050
00:37:33,590 --> 00:37:34,230
Xiaodan,

1051
00:37:35,070 --> 00:37:36,800
the two of you will do
a poetry recitation.

1052
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:38,660
Discuss the content yourselves.

1053
00:37:38,710 --> 00:37:40,370
Submit it for my review later.

1054
00:37:41,110 --> 00:37:41,920
Yes, Ms. Tong.

1055
00:37:41,980 --> 00:37:43,040
What a perfect duo.

1056
00:37:43,910 --> 00:37:45,170
Poetry recitation...

1057
00:37:45,350 --> 00:37:46,550
Which poem to recite?

1058
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:48,360
How about "If You Are Not Happy Enough"

1059
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:49,710
by Wang Guozhen?

1060
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:52,190
"If you are not happy enough,

1061
00:37:52,190 --> 00:37:54,440
don't frown and knit your brows."

1062
00:37:55,270 --> 00:37:56,870
But where is the sorrow from?

1063
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:59,130
Yeah. Where is the sorrow from?

1064
00:37:59,630 --> 00:38:00,320
I think

1065
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:01,070
at our age,

1066
00:38:01,070 --> 00:38:03,800
we shouldn't pretend to be melancholy.

1067
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:06,440
What about his other poem,
"The View from Behind"?

1068
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:08,880
"Always so simple—a silhouette."

1069
00:38:09,190 --> 00:38:10,790
-"So simple."
-That poem...

1070
00:38:12,670 --> 00:38:13,230
It was written

1071
00:38:13,230 --> 00:38:14,510
from a man's perspective.

1072
00:38:14,510 --> 00:38:15,590
It doesn't suit me.

1073
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:18,280
Then how about...

1074
00:38:18,510 --> 00:38:19,840
a poem from the Song dynasty?

1075
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:20,840
What do you think?

1076
00:38:21,010 --> 00:38:22,040
Stop playing with the bike.

1077
00:38:22,040 --> 00:38:23,030
Come up with an idea for us.

1078
00:38:23,030 --> 00:38:23,840
Yes. We need your help.

1079
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:24,590
Don't bother me with that.

1080
00:38:24,590 --> 00:38:25,840
I'm not the one going to recite a poem.

1081
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:26,480
What did you say?

1082
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:27,670
Say that again, I dare you!

1083
00:38:27,670 --> 00:38:28,630
Fine. I'll start thinking.

1084
00:38:28,630 --> 00:38:29,560
Give me the bike!

1085
00:38:30,110 --> 00:38:31,190
I-I'll catch him for you!

1086
00:38:31,190 --> 00:38:31,800
I'm on it!

1087
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:32,800
Give me the bike!

1088
00:38:32,820 --> 00:38:33,710
Why has he circled back?

1089
00:38:33,710 --> 00:38:35,000
Come after me!

1090
00:38:36,710 --> 00:38:37,320
Grandma.

1091
00:38:38,620 --> 00:38:39,150
Grandma.

1092
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:42,000
Grandma.

1093
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:44,090
What are you doing here?

1094
00:38:44,550 --> 00:38:46,610
I'm watching this stall for someone.

1095
00:38:47,920 --> 00:38:48,580
Mrs. Zhang,

1096
00:38:48,670 --> 00:38:49,360
I'm back.

1097
00:38:49,510 --> 00:38:50,240
You're back.

1098
00:38:50,470 --> 00:38:51,140
Thank you.

1099
00:38:51,290 --> 00:38:52,190
Let's go back to our place.

1100
00:38:52,190 --> 00:38:53,190
You're welcome.

1101
00:38:53,190 --> 00:38:53,590
Alright.

1102
00:38:53,590 --> 00:38:54,510
I'll head back then.

1103
00:38:54,510 --> 00:38:55,040
Let's go.

1104
00:38:55,070 --> 00:38:55,670
Alright.

1105
00:39:06,510 --> 00:39:08,800
Why did you come back alone?

1106
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:10,370
Where is Xia Lei?

1107
00:39:11,030 --> 00:39:12,890
Didn't he get off school with you?

1108
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:14,600
Xia Lei...

1109
00:39:14,620 --> 00:39:16,750
Xia Lei and Xiaodan went to rehearse

1110
00:39:17,070 --> 00:39:18,470
for a poetry recitation.

1111
00:39:18,670 --> 00:39:21,070
I had nothing to do, so I came back.

1112
00:39:23,110 --> 00:39:25,880
You came home without them just for that?

1113
00:39:27,490 --> 00:39:28,820
I wasn't of help to them.

1114
00:39:29,890 --> 00:39:31,120
You silly boy.

1115
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:32,880
Look,

1116
00:39:33,880 --> 00:39:34,920
I'm too old

1117
00:39:35,590 --> 00:39:36,630
to work

1118
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:39,440
in the factory now.

1119
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:42,000
The staff there have been nice to us.

1120
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:44,280
So, I'd often sew some small pads

1121
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:46,510
for them to wipe their hands

1122
00:39:46,530 --> 00:39:48,260
or clean the machines and such.

1123
00:39:48,500 --> 00:39:51,230
It's like I'm fighting alongside
them, isn't it?

1124
00:39:56,900 --> 00:39:57,700
Yes.

1125
00:39:58,400 --> 00:40:01,350
I can... deliver supplies
to my friends, right?

1126
00:40:01,420 --> 00:40:02,530
Exactly.

1127
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:04,720
Stick around when they practice.

1128
00:40:04,720 --> 00:40:06,880
Hand them water when they need it.

1129
00:40:07,920 --> 00:40:08,720
That's right.

1130
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:13,820
"The Revelation of Life."

1131
00:40:14,890 --> 00:40:16,260
[The Revelation of Life]

1132
00:40:15,250 --> 00:40:15,930
Xiaoman!

1133
00:40:16,670 --> 00:40:17,800
What are you doing?

1134
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:20,070
Looking for supplies for my friends.

1135
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:22,110
You've got all my old books out.

1136
00:40:22,130 --> 00:40:23,930
Don't worry. I'll put them away.

1137
00:40:24,040 --> 00:40:25,280
Make sure you tidy up the place.

1138
00:40:25,280 --> 00:40:26,010
Absolutely.

1139
00:40:33,590 --> 00:40:35,650
"Holding a Chinese lute in the arms."

1140
00:40:47,070 --> 00:40:48,670
"I must be a ceiba tree

1141
00:40:50,150 --> 00:40:51,360
beside you.

1142
00:40:53,930 --> 00:40:55,330
As a tree,

1143
00:40:55,960 --> 00:40:57,820
I'm standing together with you."

1144
00:41:00,770 --> 00:41:01,770
Have some orange.

1145
00:41:02,030 --> 00:41:03,110
You startled me.

1146
00:41:03,110 --> 00:41:04,230
What's this for, Mom?

1147
00:41:04,230 --> 00:41:05,070
I'm not eating it now.

1148
00:41:05,070 --> 00:41:06,150
Put it aside.

1149
00:41:09,060 --> 00:41:10,620
What are you writing?

1150
00:41:11,110 --> 00:41:13,070
"If I love you..."

1151
00:41:14,880 --> 00:41:15,880
I... Why did you take it?

1152
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:16,360
This...

1153
00:41:16,820 --> 00:41:18,880
"If I love you..." What's this stuff?

1154
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:20,070
It's a poem.

1155
00:41:23,710 --> 00:41:24,370
Who's this?

1156
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:27,430
Made... a line?

1157
00:41:27,460 --> 00:41:28,390
Made... a line?

1158
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:29,170
What's that?

1159
00:41:29,510 --> 00:41:31,640
You sound silly. It's an English name,

1160
00:41:32,590 --> 00:41:33,480
"Madeleine."

1161
00:41:35,150 --> 00:41:37,070
Who is this Madeleine?

1162
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:39,360
A classmate of mine.

1163
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:41,620
With an English name. Classy.

1164
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:42,960
Alright then.

1165
00:41:42,960 --> 00:41:44,670
I'll ask your teacher tomorrow.

1166
00:41:44,670 --> 00:41:46,400
I must ask your English teacher
who this is.

1167
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:47,730
P-Please don't do that.

1168
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:49,500
Don't embarrass me at school.

1169
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:50,500
Then tell me.

1170
00:41:50,500 --> 00:41:51,190
-Give it back to me.
-Tell me.

1171
00:41:51,190 --> 00:41:52,190
Who is this person?

1172
00:41:52,190 --> 00:41:54,590
Tell the truth,
and I'll give it back to you.

1173
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:55,880
Meng Ge!

1174
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:57,440
Meng Ge.

1175
00:41:59,910 --> 00:42:01,360
You've read a lot of poetry.

1176
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:03,480
Could you recommend a suitable poem for me

1177
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:05,810
and Xiaodan to recite in the variety show?

1178
00:42:06,670 --> 00:42:09,730
A suitable poem should
resonate with you spiritually.

1179
00:42:10,630 --> 00:42:12,050
Pick one from this collection.

1180
00:42:12,050 --> 00:42:14,380
Choose the one that suits you
and you like.

1181
00:42:15,230 --> 00:42:16,630
It's my deskmate Meng Ge.

1182
00:42:17,060 --> 00:42:18,590
Director Meng's daughter?

1183
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:19,800
I have to warn you.

1184
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:22,060
Y-You'd better keep a distance from her.

1185
00:42:22,280 --> 00:42:24,230
What? What are you talking about?

1186
00:42:24,230 --> 00:42:25,150
I'm not...

1187
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:26,400
You're making it sound like

1188
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:27,400
there's something going on
between me and her.

1189
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:28,240
What are you doing?

1190
00:42:28,240 --> 00:42:28,960
Don't take it away.

1191
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:30,590
I'm keeping this for the night.

1192
00:42:30,590 --> 00:42:32,030
You'll have it back tomorrow morning.

1193
00:42:32,030 --> 00:42:32,960
When you get to school

1194
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:35,180
tomorrow morning,
give it back to her right away.

1195
00:42:35,180 --> 00:42:36,800
Why? I haven't finished copying it.

1196
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:37,480
-I'm only half way through.
-Then copy

1197
00:42:37,480 --> 00:42:38,590
your Chinese textbook instead,

1198
00:42:38,590 --> 00:42:39,280
or a study guide.

1199
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:40,590
Make as many copies as you like.

1200
00:42:40,590 --> 00:42:42,360
Just don't waste time on this stuff.

1201
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:43,800
Why should I copy a textbook?

1202
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:45,150
Mom, g-give it back to me!
